      <section eId="sec_13_8_39">
        <num>13-8-39</num>
        <content>
          <p>It shall be unlawful for the manufacturer or franchisor, without due cause, to fail to renew on terms then equally available to all its wholesalers, to terminate a franchise, or to restrict the transfer of a franchise unless the franchisee shall receive fair and reasonable compensation for the inventory of the business.As used in this Code section, "due cause" shall be construed in accordance with the definition of same as contained in subparagraph (c)(3)(B) of Code Section 13-8-35.</p>
        </content>
      </section>
